cs.SI, cs.CY, cs.SOC, cs.IR, cs.HC 

The paper focuses on the use of social cues and peer affiliations in social advertising, which falls under the category of social influence. Therefore, cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses user interface design and ad optimization, which could fall under cs.CY (Computers and Society) and cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction). The experiments involve measuring ad performance, which could be related to cs.IR (Information Retrieval). Finally, the paper touches on central questions in social science research, which could be related to cs.SOC (Social and Economic Networks).
